oracle.iam.identity.icf.connector.openfire

Class Provider<T extends Entity>

  • java.lang.Object
    • oracle.iam.identity.icf.foundation.logging.AbstractLoggable
      • oracle.iam.identity.icf.connector.openfire.Provider<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    oracle.iam.identity.icf.foundation.logging.Loggable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FlagProvider, GroupProvider, MemberProvider, PropertyProvider, PropertyProvider.System, RoomMateProvider, RoomProvider, UserProvider

    public abstract class Provider<T extends Entity>
extends oracle.iam.identity.icf.foundation.logging.AbstractLoggable
    The descriptor to handle entities.

    This object contains factory methods for each Java provider interface and Java element interface generated in the oracle.iam.identity.sysauthz.schema package.

    There is only one existing instance of the class in a JVM; it is implemented as singleton.

    Since:
    1.0.0.0
    Version:
    1.0.0.0

      • Provider

        protected Provider(Context context,
                   java.lang.String name)
            throws oracle.iam.identity.icf.foundation.SystemException
        Constructs a Provider that operates on the specified Context context to maintain the entity for the given name.

        The DatabaseEntity required is obtaind by querying the schema definition of the specified Context context.

        Parameters:
        context - the Context where the provider operates on.
        Allowed object is Context.
        name - the name of the entity to access.
        Allowed object is String.
        Throws:
        oracle.iam.identity.icf.foundation.SystemException - if the schema operation fails.

        Reads all entities from the Service Provider that matches the specified filter criteria.
        The returned collection is limited to the records between startRow and lastRow and can be less than lastRow - startRow.

        Allowed object is long.
